(c | t | w | a) coord display/read mode: Coord,TCoord,WCoord,All
(n | c | # | a) who display/read mode: Names, Colors, Numbers, All
( sandbox ) sets all players to human and the map to reveal all
safe creates lots of machine guns around every human capital
pointer [text] displays a popup with 'text' pointing at the crrent mouse position
netcmd [console command] sends a 'console command' to all players via an issue.
(script [load (filename) | run (script name) | check]) Assumes .bhs extension, or check all funcs
(eval <numeric expression or function call>) -- executes a script expression (no vars, etc...)
(vtune (start | stop | load)) starts or stops recording VTUNE(TM) data if a session is currently open and paused. Use load to map DLL if needed

(commerce [level] [who]) show or change commerce level for nation
(science [level] [who]) show or change science level for nation

( camera [x,y] shows or sets camera position
( [start | stop] [base_path_and_filename] ) to start and stop capturing screen sequences

( anim # ) make selected units run a specific animation
( damage (o[,who] | select) [+|-]damage ) adjust damage to object or all selected
( move (o[,who] | select) (x,y | cursor) ) move object or selection

( add [#] typename [who=RED] [x,y]) insert unit or building at mouse loc

Drop a Wild Bird at Mouse
( nuke ) Drop a Nuke at mouse position

( deploy ) Deploys the currently selected unit(s), if they are deploying units

(mapsize [size | ?]) queries or sets size of map for map generator
(mapstyle [size | ?] queries or sets style for map generator)
(numplayers [num]) queries or sets number of players for single player map generator
(restart [<seed>|same|random]) restarts the game. <Seed>=explicit seed, same=use same, random=random seed. Default is random.
(seed [seed]) Queries or sets master game seed
(startareas) how much forest and rock is within each player's starting city radius
(region [id]) Info on land or sea region (specified by # or at cursor)
(tileset [reload]) Force tileset textures to flush and reload.
(trans [ show ]) show transition codes for current wcoord
(river [ start | grow | calc ]) start a new river | add a new wcoord control point to the current river | compute a river
